Class OutputPlugin

java.lang.Object
  ca.mcgill.hs.plugin.OutputPlugin
All Implemented Interfaces:
Plugin, java.lang.Runnable
Direct Known Subclasses:
FileOutput, LocationClusterer, ScreenOutput, SimpleClassifierPlugin, TestMagOutputPlugin
public abstract class OutputPlugin
extends java.lang.Object
implements Plugin, java.lang.Runnable

Abstract class to be extended by all OutputPlugins. Provides an interface for using OutputPlugins.

Method Detail

getPreferences

public static Preference[] getPreferences()
This method returns an array of Preference objects for the given OutputPlugin. By default, this method returns null. If a specific OutputPlugin wants to define Preferences, they must override this method.

Returns:
An array of the Preferences of this object.

hasPreferences

public static boolean hasPreferences()
Returns whether or not this OutputPlugin has Preferences. By default, this method returns false. If a given OutputPlugin overrides the getPreferences(Context) method, they must also override this method to let it return true.

Returns:
Whether or not this OutputPlugin has preferences.

onDataReady

public final void onDataReady(DataPacket packet)
Called when a DataPacket is sent from an InputPlugin. Adds the DataPacket that is now ready to dpList.

Parameters:
packet - The DataPacket that is ready to be received.

onPluginStart

protected abstract void onPluginStart()
Called when this OutputPlugin is started. This method is meant to be overridden.

onPluginStop

protected abstract void onPluginStop()
Called when this OutputPlugin is stopped. This method is meant to be overridden.

onPreferenceChanged

public void onPreferenceChanged()
Signals the plugin that preferences have changed. OutputPlugin objects with preferences should override this method if something changes at runtime when preferences change. If this method is not overridden in a new plugin implementation, the preferences for that plugin will only update the next time the service is started.

run

public void run()
Used by the ThreadPool to continuously retrieved DataPackets from dpList. The DataPacket are passed to onDataReceived() one at a time for as long as this plugin is running and dpList is not empty.

run in interface java.lang.Runnable
